edu.xtec.jclic.bags

Class JumpInfo

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.xtec.jclic.bags.JumpInfo
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Domable, Cloneable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ActivitySequenceJump, ConditionalJumpInfo

    public class JumpInfo
extends Object
implements Domable, Cloneable
    This class contains information about what the sequence manager of JClic must do in specific circumstances: when an activity finishes, when the user clicks on the "next" and "prev" buttons, or when a special active content is activated. Different kinds of actions are possible: to go back to a previous point in the sequence, to exit the program, to stop (do nothing), to jump to a specific point in the sequence of activities or to jump to another JClic project.
    Version:
    13.09.10
    Author:
    Francesc Busquets (fbusquets@xtec.cat)
